Method Detail

sampleCurve

public static double[] sampleCurve(Curve curve,
                                   double xMax,
                                   double samplePeriod)
Returns a double[] containing a sampled version of curve. Curve is sampled within 0 <= x <= xMax, with a sample period of samplePeriod. To plot the sample curve in Matlab, the following command can be used: plot([0:samplePeriod:xMax],MatlabUtil.sampleCurve(curve,xMax,samplePeriod),'b.')

Parameters:
curve - the Curve to sample.
xMax - the upper x-value of the sample range.
samplePeriod - the sample period.
Returns:
a sampled version of curve.

importFromSimulink

public static Curve importFromSimulink(double[][] data)
Creates a Curve from a double[][] that was previously exported using the exportToSimulink(Curve) method.
data has the following encoding:
  data[0][0] = Length of aperiodic part
  data[0][1] = Length of periodic part
  data[0][2] = period    
  data[1][0] = px0
  data[1][1] = py0
  data[1][2] = pdy
  data[2][0] = pds
  data[2][1] = pyMin
  data[2][2] = pyMax
  ...
  data[i][0] = segment.x
  data[i][1] = segment.y
  data[i][2] = segment.s
  ...

Parameters:
data - a double[][] containiing the curve data.
Returns:
a Curve created from data.

exportToSimulink

public static double[][] exportToSimulink(Curve c)
Exports a Curve to a double[][] representation.
The returned data has the following encoding:
  data[0][0] = Length of aperiodic part
  data[0][1] = Length of periodic part
  data[0][2] = period    
  data[1][0] = px0
  data[1][1] = py0
  data[1][2] = pdy
  data[2][0] = pds
  data[2][1] = pyMin
  data[2][2] = pyMax
  ...
  data[i][0] = segment.x
  data[i][1] = segment.y
  data[i][2] = segment.s
  ...

Parameters:
c - the Curve to export
Returns:
a double[][] encoding the Curve data.

setSimulinkDataLength

public static void setSimulinkDataLength(int len)
Sets the length of the double[][] that is used to represent a Curve in Simulink. Curves are represented in Simulink using an double array of size double[len][3]
